<subSubSection id="2B996578FFD2FFDE1ED13C7AFAD5F9BA" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFD2FFDE1ED13C7AFE94FAF1" blockId="6.[189,310,1378,1404]" box="[189,310,1378,1404]" pageId="6" pageNumber="32">
<heading id="3874819FFFD2FFDE1ED13C7AFE94FAF1" bold="true" box="[189,310,1378,1404]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" reason="3">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFD2FFDE1ED13C7AFE94FAF1" bold="true" box="[189,310,1378,1404]" pageId="6" pageNumber="32">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFD2FFDE1ED13C88FAD5F9BA" blockId="6.[189,1401,1424,1592]" pageId="6" pageNumber="32">
The female of 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFD2FFDE1F163C88FDD3FA27" authority="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira, 2021" authorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" authorityYear="2021" box="[378,625,1424,1450]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Kryptochroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFD2FFDE1F163C88FDD3FA27" box="[378,625,1424,1450]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="32">Kryptochroma gigas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4AC4579AFFD2FFDE1C123C89FC9DFA26" box="[638,831,1425,1451]" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
resembles those of 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFD2FFDE1A533C89FB70FA27" authority="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira, 2021" authorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" authorityYear="2021" box="[1087,1234,1424,1450]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Kryptochroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadrata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFD2FFDE1A533C89FB70FA27" box="[1087,1234,1424,1450]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="32">K. quadrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4AC4579AFFD2FFDE1AB33C89FA9DFA26" box="[1247,1343,1425,1451]" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFD2FFDE1ED13CACFECCFA43" authorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Mello-Leitao" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[189,366,1460,1486]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Kryptochroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pentacantha">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFD2FFDE1ED13CACFECCFA43" box="[189,366,1460,1486]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="32">K. pentacantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its large body size, which is significantly larger than in the other species here described. 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFD2FFDE1ED13CCFFE13FA7C" authority="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira, 2021" authorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,433,1495,1521]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Kryptochroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFD2FFDE1ED13CCFFE13FA7C" box="[189,433,1495,1521]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="32">Kryptochroma gigas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4AC4579AFFD2FFDE1FD03CCFFDD1FA7C" box="[444,627,1495,1521]" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished by the elevated and short opisthosoma and by the heart-shaped epigynal plate with a short and stout projection over a wide median septum, which divides the median field in two longitudinal gutters reaching the copulatory openings (
<figureCitation id="FBB82A76FFD2FFDE1AC73F05FA85F9BA" box="[1195,1319,1565,1591]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1004,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-210@7.[189,1398,1004,1882]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Female of Kryptochroma gigas Machado &amp; Viecelli gen. et sp. nov. Holotype (UFMG 4734). A. Habitus, dorsal view (arrows indicate the pair of circular taints on the posterior slope of the prosoma). B. Front. C, E. Epigynal plate, ventral view. D, F. Spermathecae, dorsal view." pageId="6" pageNumber="32">Figs 3C–F</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="FBB82A76FFD2FFDE1B5F3F05FACBF9BA" box="[1331,1385,1565,1591]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="34.[189,232,1912,1938]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,299,1849]" captionTargetId="figure-11@34.[189,1398,276,1861]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Fig. 21. Illustrations of epigynum in ventral and dorsal view. A. Kryptochroma gigas Machado &amp; Viecelli gen. et sp. nov., holotype (UFMG 4734). B. K. hilaris Machado &amp; Teixeira gen. et sp. nov., holotype (MPEG 13322). C. K. parahybana (Mello-Leitão, 1929) gen. et comb. nov. (MPEG 30339)." pageId="6" pageNumber="32">21A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2B996578FFD2FFDE1ED13F47FDB2F946" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFD2FFDE1ED13F47FEE6F9F4" blockId="6.[189,324,1631,1657]" box="[189,324,1631,1657]" pageId="6" pageNumber="32">
<heading id="3874819FFFD2FFDE1ED13F47FEE6F9F4" bold="true" box="[189,324,1631,1657]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="32" reason="3">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFD2FFDE1ED13F47FEE6F9F4" bold="true" box="[189,324,1631,1657]" pageId="6" pageNumber="32">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFD2FFDE1ED13F95FDB2F946" blockId="6.[187,1399,1677,1739]" pageId="6" pageNumber="32">The epithet is a Latin feminine noun that means giant, referring to the bigger size of this species compared to other species of the genus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
