<heading id="3874819FFFD3FFDF1ED13810FEECFEAF" bold="true" box="[189,334,264,290]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" reason="3">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFD3FFDF1ED13810FEECFEAF" bold="true" box="[189,334,264,290]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFD3FFDF1E86382FFDCFFEDC" blockId="7.[189,1400,311,478]" box="[234,621,311,337]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFD3FFDF1E86382FFEE7FEDC" bold="true" box="[234,325,311,337]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">Female</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus id="BC388851FFD3FFDF1F39382FFE62FEDC" box="[341,448,311,337]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">holotype</typeStatus>
, UFMG 4734)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFD3FFDF1ED13843FEF0FE53" blockId="7.[189,1400,311,478]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">
PROSOMA. Anterior eye row very recurved and posterior slightly procurved; prosoma dark yellow with large lateral black taints, median region and posterior slope yellow, contoured by black lines (
<figureCitation id="FBB82A76FFD3FFDF1B623865FF71FE36" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1004,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-210@7.[189,1398,1004,1882]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Female of Kryptochroma gigas Machado &amp; Viecelli gen. et sp. nov. Holotype (UFMG 4734). A. Habitus, dorsal view (arrows indicate the pair of circular taints on the posterior slope of the prosoma). B. Front. C, E. Epigynal plate, ventral view. D, F. Spermathecae, dorsal view." pageId="7" pageNumber="33">Fig. 3A– B</figureCitation>
). Chelicerae dark yellow with black stains, endites and labium black, sternum black with a median yellow taint.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFD3FFDF1ED13B1EFE69FDCF" blockId="7.[189,1398,517,578]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">LEGS. Femora I and II dorsally enlarged and with many setiferous tubercles, femora III and IV bicolor, half black, half yellow.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFD3FFDF1ED13B72FBF7FD2A" blockId="7.[189,1399,618,680]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">
OPISTHOSOMA. Predominantly dark-yellow, black on the back of the abdominal projections and on the sides, rough surfaced and slightly concave on the anterior border (
<figureCitation id="FBB82A76FFD3FFDF1DAA3B95FBEAFD2A" box="[966,1096,653,679]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1920,1946]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1004,1882]" captionTargetId="figure-210@7.[189,1398,1004,1882]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Female of Kryptochroma gigas Machado &amp; Viecelli gen. et sp. nov. Holotype (UFMG 4734). A. Habitus, dorsal view (arrows indicate the pair of circular taints on the posterior slope of the prosoma). B. Front. C, E. Epigynal plate, ventral view. D, F. Spermathecae, dorsal view." pageId="7" pageNumber="33">Fig. 3A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFD3FFDF1ED13BD7FAD4FCF8" blockId="7.[189,1400,718,886]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">MEASUREMENTS. Eye diameters and eye interdistances:AME 0.09,ALE 0.14, PME 0.12, PLE 0.12, AME– AME 0.08, AME–ALE 0.12, PME–PME 0.24, PME–PLE 0.06, MOQ length 0.43, MOQ width 0.48; leg formula: 1-2-4-3: leg I – femur 4.66/ patella 2.59/ tibiae 3.10/ metatarsus 2.17/ tarsus 1.29/ total 13.81; II – 3.83/ 2.07/ 2.84/ 1.86/ 1.29/ 11.89; III – 2.07/ 1.29/ 1.86/ 1.19/ 0.82/ 7.23; IV – 2.59/ 1.19/ 1.86/ 1.29/ 0.82/ 7.75. Total body length 9.62; prosoma 4.40 length, 4.04 width; opisthosoma</paragraph>
<caption id="37FC667BFFD3FFDF1ED13E98FBF3F86C" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" startId="7.[189,232,1920,1946]" targetBox="[189,1398,1004,1882]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFD3FFDF1ED13E98FBF3F86C" blockId="7.[188,1399,1920,2017]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFD3FFDF1ED13E98FEAFF817" bold="true" box="[189,269,1920,1946]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">Fig. 3.</emphasis>
Female of 
<taxonomicName id="A4834D70FFD3FFDF1FF63E98FC27F817" authority="Machado &amp; Viecelli" authorityName="Machado &amp; Viecelli &amp; Guzati &amp; Grismado &amp; Teixeira" authorityYear="2021" box="[410,901,1920,1947]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Kryptochroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas" status="gen. et sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFD3FFDF1FF63E98FD2FF817" box="[410,653,1920,1946]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">Kryptochroma gigas</emphasis>
Machado &amp; Viecelli
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4AC4579AFFD3FFDF1DE23E99FBE6F816" box="[910,1092,1921,1947]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" rank="species">gen. et sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
Holotype (UFMG 4734). 
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFD3FFDF1ED33EBBFF70F830" bold="true" box="[191,210,1955,1981]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">A</emphasis>
. Habitus, dorsal view (arrows indicate the pair of circular taints on the posterior slope of the prosoma). 
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFD3FFDF1ED03EDFFF72F86C" bold="true" box="[188,208,1991,2017]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">B</emphasis>
. Front. 
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFD3FFDF1F413EDFFEC7F86C" bold="true" box="[301,357,1991,2017]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">C, E</emphasis>
. Epigynal plate, ventral view. 
<emphasis id="51F7EAE1FFD3FFDF1CA73EDFFCA3F86C" bold="true" box="[715,769,1991,2017]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33">D, F</emphasis>
. Spermathecae, dorsal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="633C36F3FFDCFFD01ED13811FD8CFECB" blockId="8.[189,1398,265,327]" pageId="8" pageNumber="34">length 4.62; clypeus 0.37 height; sternum 1.45 length, 1.20 width; endites 0.69 length, 0.40 width; labium 0.48 length, 0.53 width.</paragraph>
